<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:lang="en-US" xml:id="exponents-summary">
  <title>Summary of the Rules of Exponents</title>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          The Product Rule for Exponents:  <me>x^m \cdot x^n=x^{m+n}</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The Power to a Power Rule for Exponents: <me>(x^m)^n=x^{mn}</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The Product to a Power Rule for Exponents: <me>(xy)^n=x^ny^n</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The Quotient to a Power Rule for Exponents: <me>\left(\frac{x}{y}\right)^n=\frac{x^n}{y^n}</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The Quotient Rules for Exponents: <me>\frac{x^m}{x^n}=x^{m-n} \text{ and } \frac{x^m}{x^n}=\frac{1}{x^{n-m}}</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Zero Exponent: <me>x^0=1 \text{ for } x \neq 0</me>
        </p>
     </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Negative Exponents: <me>x^{-n}=\frac{1}{x^n}</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Properties if Negative Exponents: <me>\frac{1}{x^{-n}}=x^n \text{ and } \left(\frac{x}{y}\right)^{-n}=\left(\frac{y}{x}\right)^n</me>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>

</section>
